he software development life cycle\nBULLET::::- Computer-assisted structure elucidation, the use of computers to elucidate molecular structures\nBULLET::::- Switch statement, a control statement in computer programming\nBULLET::::- Use case, in software engineering and systems engineering; a description of a system’s behaviour as it responds to requests\nBULLET::::- Case study, examination of a single instance or event\nBULLET::::- Case-hardening, a process of hardening the surface of a metal object\nBULLET::::- Case-shot, a type of anti-personnel canister ammunition similar to a shrapnel shell\nBULLET::::- A trouble ticket, also known as a support case, in an issue tracking system\nBULLET::::- Proof by exhaustion, a method of mathematical proof also known as \"proof by cases\"\nBULLET::::- Contribution to ARIEL Spectroscopy of Exoplanets (CASE), an instrument on the European space telescope ARIEL\n\nBULLET::::- Case Middle School, part of Punahou School in Oahu, Hawaii\nBULLET::::- Case Western Reserve University, an independent research university in Cleveland, Ohio, US\nBULLET::::- Center for Advanced Studies in Engineering, now Sir Syed CASE Institute of Technology, a private engineering institute in Islamabad, Pakistan\nBULLET::::- Center for Architecture, Science and Ecology, a research facility of the Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute, US\nBULLET::::- Centre for Christian Apologetics, Scholarship and Education, a ministry of New College, University of New South Wales\nBULLET::::- Council for Advancement and Support of Education, a nonprofit association of educational institutions, US\n\nBULLET::::- Case Corporation, defunct manufacturer of agricultural equipment, tractors and cars\nBULLET::::- Case Construction Equipment (Case CE), a manufacturer of construction equipment\nBULLET::::- Case IH, a manufacturer of agricultural equipment\nBULLET::::- W. R. Case & Sons Cutlery Co., an American manufacturer of knives\n\nBULLET::::- Conceptually Accurate Signed Engli